==Ancient Greek==
===Etymology===
From Indo-European ''*di̯ēus''.  Cognate with Sanskrit [[द्यौष्]] (dyáuṣ), Latin [[Iovis]], Germanic ''*Tiwaz'' (Old English [[Tiw|Tīw]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʣeus/}}

===Noun===
'''Ζεύς'''

# [[Zeus]]

